872
01:02:55,240 --> 01:02:57,356
What about the photographs?

873
01:02:57,440 --> 01:03:00,876
Oh, don't worry.
I'll ask you to do me a favour

874
01:03:00,960 --> 01:03:03,030
and it'll be one you'll enjoy.

875
01:03:03,120 --> 01:03:05,714
You'll get the negatives back then.

876
01:03:08,080 --> 01:03:11,550
But in the meantime, strength.

877
01:03:13,320 --> 01:03:15,390
Here's a little gift...

878
01:03:16,480 --> 01:03:18,630
from Heather to Heather.

879
01:03:58,400 --> 01:03:59,992
- Guess who.
- Heather?

880
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:19,439
'Hello? '

881
01:04:19,520 --> 01:04:21,158
Hello, Betty? This is Veronica.

882
01:04:24,840 --> 01:04:27,400
I don't believe it, I'm winning!

883
01:04:28,720 --> 01:04:31,473
Don't you start getting cocky on me, girl.

884
01:04:33,240 --> 01:04:35,470
I really missed you.

885
01:04:35,560 --> 01:04:38,597
I know I'm not as exciting as
your other friends.

886
01:04:38,680 --> 01:04:40,636
That is bullshit.

887
01:04:40,720 --> 01:04:42,676
Shoot.

888
01:04:42,760 --> 01:04:45,035
Do you know I'm still a virgin?

889
01:04:45,120 --> 01:04:48,192
OK, I French-kissed Al Springer once.

890
01:04:48,280 --> 01:04:50,236
It was a total disaster.

891
01:04:50,320 --> 01:04:53,232
Shoot the ball.

892
01:04:55,760 --> 01:05:00,629
Betty, your daydreams are a lot better than
my realities, believe me.

893
01:05:03,200 --> 01:05:06,272
But now, prepare to die.

894
01:05:06,360 --> 01:05:08,112
Ronnie.

895
01:05:23,240 --> 01:05:25,993
You're not just going for those two shots.

896
01:05:26,080 --> 01:05:29,709
I mean, go ahead, knock me out.
It's the only way to win.

897
01:05:31,400 --> 01:05:33,675
It's not my style.

898
01:05:33,760 --> 01:05:37,514
Nice guys finish last, I should know.

899
01:05:46,160 --> 01:05:47,513
Bravo.

900
01:05:48,600 --> 01:05:50,318
Bravo.

901
01:05:51,400 --> 01:05:53,960
Listen, I got to get home, OK?

902
01:05:54,040 --> 01:05:56,156
OK.

903
01:05:56,240 --> 01:05:58,037
Thanks.

904
01:05:58,120 --> 01:05:59,997
Bye, Betty.

905
01:06:00,080 --> 01:06:01,513
Bye.

906
01:06:01,600 --> 01:06:04,512
Betty, leaving so soon?

907
01:06:04,600 --> 01:06:06,158
I'm red.

908
01:06:33,480 --> 01:06:37,553
'The Westerburg suicides
were tough on all of us,

909
01:06:37,640 --> 01:06:42,350
'but we shared the pain of losing
three very popular students.

910
01:06:42,440 --> 01:06:46,069
'I came into the cafeteria,
asked them to hold hands... '

911
01:06:46,160 --> 01:06:48,993
Isn't that that flake
we met at the open house?

912
01:06:49,080 --> 01:06:51,389
'... burst of cleansing synchronicity,

913
01:06:51,480 --> 01:06:54,870
'TV cameras happened
onto our path and captured... '

914
01:06:54,960 --> 01:06:57,520
Cleansing synchronicity?

915
01:06:57,600 --> 01:07:01,388
Outpouring of emotion?

916
01:07:01,480 --> 01:07:03,789
Ha! Look! There's Heather.

917
01:07:05,040 --> 01:07:07,713
There's Heather. Where are you, Veronica?

918
01:07:07,800 --> 01:07:13,511
'Before a teenager decides to kill himself,
there are certain facts that he should know.

919
01:07:13,600 --> 01:07:19,391
'After all, this decision affects all of us
and there's only one chance to get it right.'

920
01:07:32,240 --> 01:07:34,196
'Getting some supervi... '

921
01:07:34,280 --> 01:07:36,111
Turn that back on.

922
01:07:36,200 --> 01:07:38,509
These programmes are eating suicide up.

923
01:07:38,600 --> 01:07:41,433
