a cool thing to do.

924
01:07:41,520 --> 01:07:46,469
Are you trying to tell me it's not a time
for troubled youth? Stand up straight.

925
01:07:46,560 --> 01:07:49,757
All we want is to be
treated like human beings,

926
01:07:49,840 --> 01:07:52,354
not patronised like bunny rabbits.

927
01:07:52,440 --> 01:07:54,590
I don't patronise bunny rabbits.

928
01:07:54,680 --> 01:07:56,671
Treated like human beings?

929
01:07:56,760 --> 01:08:00,514
Is that what you said,
little Miss Voice-of-a-generation?

930
01:08:00,600 --> 01:08:03,831
How do you think adults
act with other adults?

931
01:08:03,920 --> 01:08:06,593
You think it's all just
a game of doubles tennis?

932
01:08:06,680 --> 01:08:10,116
When teenagers complain
they want to be treated like human beings,

933
01:08:10,200 --> 01:08:12,998
it's because they are
being treated like human beings.

934
01:08:13,080 --> 01:08:17,551
Well, I guess I picked the wrong time
to be a human being.

935
01:08:17,640 --> 01:08:19,631
Well, you'll live.

936
01:08:25,760 --> 01:08:27,716
Want some pâté?

937
01:08:29,800 --> 01:08:32,234
Hi, everybody. Door was open.

938
01:08:32,320 --> 01:08:34,675
Veronica, have you heard?

939
01:08:34,760 --> 01:08:37,115
We were doing Chinese at the food fair

940
01:08:37,200 --> 01:08:40,510
when we heard Martha Dumptruck
tried to buy the farm.

941
01:08:40,600 --> 01:08:44,434
She belly-flopped in front of a car
wearing a suicide note.

942
01:08:45,440 --> 01:08:47,192
Is she dead?

943
01:08:47,280 --> 01:08:50,955
No. That's the punch line.
She's in stable condition.

944
01:08:51,040 --> 01:08:56,068
Just another case of a geek trying to imitate
the popular people and failing miserably.

945
01:08:56,160 --> 01:08:58,116
Is that pâté?

946
01:09:02,160 --> 01:09:05,630
- I said I was sorry.
- You were out of control.

947
01:09:05,720 --> 01:09:08,792
